A few years ago I did Turbo Fire HIIIT workouts for 3 months straight. I loved it. Then one day my knee cap felt like it moved to the left a little. I instantly stopped as I didn’t want to totally injure myself. My knee healed with rest. Since Dec 28, 2019 - my husband and I do a medium to fast paced walk each morning - up to 1 1/2 hrs. It is so nice to go for a walk along a bush track, breath in fresh air and hear the animals. Much easier on the body and still getting a good workout. Every so often I do yoga for stretching and for how it makes you feel afterwards.  Thanks for sharing your fitness and health tips 🌸🌿
